Just because he eventually realised making money off selling weapons is bad doesn’t excuse that he did and I understand if some people still have issue with it. But then they parade steve as morally superior when 1) he’s an american soldier who costume is the us flag 2) the literal embodiment of american exceptionalism

summary: If you don’t like tony stark because of his history of war profiteering then by virtue you cannot like rhodey, steve and bucky...
question: If you don’t like tony stark because of his history of war profiteering then by virtue you cannot like rhodey, steve and bucky because they are all part of the american military industrial complex with tony, steve and rhodey being at the top. It doesn’t make any sense that you don’t like the guy who makes the weapon but take no issue with the colonel who buys the weapon in masses for the us army and the captain and soldier who use those weapons to protect and spread american imperialism

its also kinda. kinda sorta funny that tony dropped the weapons industry back in iron man 1 and spent ten years redeeming himself and none of these other characters did that ever yet yall somehow forgive them but not tony? (not that bucky needs to redeem himself tho)

A Steve kidnaps Tony love story full of plot holes because the author needed some comfort after reading a bunch of Tony/Steve angsty fanfics where one of them always dies.

There’s a Doctor Strange movie from 1978 that they hoped would turn into a TV show. Even if you’re 100% sober all the time, that movie’s special effects will make you feel like you’re on drugs, and while it could pass for a G-rating, something about the acting makes it feel…
